  "local_port": 56984,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Certainly! A 4-ounce steak can be wonderfully versatile in various dishes, offering both quick meals and more elaborate preparations. Here are several recipes that make the most of a 4-ounce steak:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Classic Steak Salad**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (such as sirloin or flank)\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 4 cups mixed salad greens\n- \u00bd cup cherry tomatoes, halved\n- \u00bc red onion, thinly sliced\n- \u00bc cucumber, sliced\n- \u00bc cup crumbled feta or blue cheese\n- Optional: avocado slices or nuts (e.g., walnuts, almonds)\n\n**For the Dressing:**\n- 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar\n- 1 teaspoon Dijon mustard\n- \u00bc cup olive oil\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Prepare the Steak:**\n   - Season the steak on both sides with salt and pepper.\n   - Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n   - Cook the steak for about 3-4 minutes per side for medium-rare, or until desired doneness.\n   - Remove from heat and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing thinly against the grain.\n\n2. **Assemble the Salad:**\n   - In a large bowl, combine salad greens, cherry tomatoes, red onion, cucumber, and cheese.\n   - Add the sliced steak on top.\n\n3. **Make the Dressing:**\n   - In a small bowl or jar, whisk together balsamic vinegar, Dijon mustard, olive oil, salt, and pepper until emulsified.\n\n4. **Serve:**\n   - Drizzle the dressing over the salad just before serving.\n   - Add optional toppings like avocado slices or nuts for extra flavor and texture.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Beef Tacos**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (flank or skirt works well)\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 4 small tortillas (corn or flour)\n- \u00bc cup chopped onion\n- \u00bc cup chopped cilantro\n- 1 lime, cut into wedges\n- Optional toppings: salsa, guacamole, shredded cheese, sour cream\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Cook the Steak:**\n   - Season the steak with salt and pepper.\n   - Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over high heat.\n   - Cook the steak for about 3 minutes per side for medium-rare.\n   - Let it rest for a few minutes, then slice thinly against the grain.\n\n2. **Prepare Toppings:**\n   - Chop onions and cilantro.\n   - Warm the tortillas in a dry skillet or microwave until pliable.\n\n3. **Assemble the Tacos:**\n   - Place sliced steak on each tortilla.\n   - Top with chopped onions, cilantro, and any additional desired toppings.\n   - Squeeze a wedge of lime over each taco before serving.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Steak and Cheese Quesadilla**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak, thinly sliced\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- 1 teaspoon olive oil\n- 2 large flour tortillas\n- \u00bd cup shredded cheese (cheddar, Monterey Jack, or a blend)\n- \u00bc cup sliced bell peppers (optional)\n- \u00bc cup sliced onions (optional)\n- Salsa and sour cream, for serving\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Cook the Steak:**\n   - Season the steak with salt and pepper.\n   - Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n   - Add steak slices and cook until browned, about 2-3 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n\n2. **Cook Vegetables (Optional):**\n   - In the same skillet, add bell peppers and onions.\n   - Saut\u00e9 until softened, about 4-5 minutes.\n\n3. **Assemble the Quesadilla:**\n   - Place one tortilla in a clean skillet over medium heat.\n   - Sprinkle half of the shredded cheese evenly over the tortilla.\n   - Add the cooked steak and vegetables (if using).\n   - Top with the remaining cheese and the second tortilla.\n\n4. **Cook the Quesadilla:**\n   - Cook until the bottom tortilla is golden brown, then carefully flip.\n   - Cook the other side until golden and the cheese is melted, about 2-3 minutes.\n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Remove from skillet, slice into wedges, and serve with salsa and sour cream.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Stir-Fry Beef and Vegetables**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak, thinly sliced against the grain\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n- 1 tablespoon vegetable oil\n- 1 cup mixed vegetables (broccoli, bell peppers, snap peas, carrots)\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 teaspoon ginger, grated\n- 2 tablespoons oyster sauce or hoisin sauce\n- Cooked rice or noodles, for serving\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Marinate the Beef:**\n   - In a bowl, combine sliced steak with soy sauce and cornstarch. Let it sit for 10-15 minutes.\n\n2. **Cook the Beef:**\n   - Heat vegetable oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.\n   - Add the marinated beef and stir-fry until browned, about 2-3 minutes. Remove and set aside.\n\n3. **Cook Vegetables:**\n   - In the same wok, add a bit more oil if needed.\n   - Add minced garlic and grated ginger; saut\u00e9 for about 30 seconds until fragrant.\n   - Add mixed vegetables and stir-fry until tender-crisp, about 4-5 minutes.\n\n4. **Combine and Sauce:**\n   - Return the beef to the wok.\n   - Add oyster or hoisin sauce and toss everything together until well coated and heated through.\n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Serve the stir-fry over cooked rice or noodles.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Steak Sandwich with Caramelized Onions**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 4 oz steak (ribeye or sirloin), seasoned with salt and pepper\n- 1 tablespoon olive oil\n- 1 large onion, thinly sliced\n- 2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar\n- 2 slices of your favorite bread or a baguette\n- 2 slices provolone or Swiss cheese\n- Optional: arugula, horseradish sauce, or mustard\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Cook the Steak:**\n   - Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n   - Cook the steak for about 3-4 minutes per side for medium-rare.\n   - Let it rest for a few minutes, then slice thinly.\n\n2. **Caramelize the Onions:**\n   - In the same skillet, lower the heat to medium.\n   - Add the sliced onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until they begin to soften, about 5 minutes.\n   - Add balsamic vinegar and continue to cook until onions are deeply caramelized, about another 10-15 minutes. If they start to stick, add a splash of water.\n\n3. **Assemble the Sandwich:**\n   - Toast the bread slices until golden.\n   - Layer the sliced steak on one slice of bread.\n   - Top with caramelized onions and cheese.\n   - Add any optional toppings like arugula or a spread of horseradish sauce.\n\n4. **Melt the Cheese:**\n   - Place the assembled sandwich back in the skillet or a sandwich press.\n   - Cook until the cheese melts and the sandwich is heated through, about 2-3 minutes per side.\n\n5. **Serve:**\n   - Slice in half and enjoy warm.\n\n---\n\n### Cooking Tips for a 4-Ounce Steak:\n\n- **Choose the Right Cut:** Tender cuts like sirloin, flank, or ribeye work best for quick recipes. Ensure the steak is thinly sliced for faster cooking and tenderness.\n  \n- **Marinating:** Even a short marinade (15-30 minutes) can enhance flavor and tenderness, especially for leaner cuts.\n  \n- **Resting the Steak:** Let the cooked steak rest for a few minutes before slicing to retain juices and ensure maximum flavor.\n  \n- **High Heat:** Cooking steak on high heat helps develop a flavorful crust quickly without overcooking the inside.\n\n- **Season Well:** Simple seasoning with salt and pepper often suffices, but feel free to experiment with herbs and spices like garlic powder, paprika, or rosemary.\n\n---\n\nThese recipes are adaptable and can be adjusted based on your personal preferences and available ingredients. Enjoy experimenting with your 4-ounce steak in these delicious dishes!",
